[S. F. No. 16221. In Bank. Apr. 2, 1942.] In re JOSEPH P. LACEY for Readmission to The State Bar of California.

[Former denial of application for readmission (11 Cal. (2d) 699).]

Edwin V. McKenzie, Walter E. Hettman, Edward P. Murphy and Leo Friedman for Petitioner. *895THE COURT.

In accordance with the report and recommendation of the Board of Governors of The State Bar of California, it is ordered that Joseph P. Lacey be reinstated as a member of The State Bar of California, upon payment of the fees and taking the oath required by law.
